{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EVwkdSkyb3KT8NRmMoGh7k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## US-029 - Dead Particle Compaction\n\n### Files changed:\n- **`fallingsand3d/world.py`** - Added `World.compact()` method using CuPy stream compaction (`flatnonzero` + fancy indexing gather). Also fixed `num_active` property to use `(packed_info & 0xFF) != 0` instead of `packed_info != 0` to correctly handle dead particles with `packed_info=0x300`.\n- **`fallingsand3d/simulation.py`** - Added `compact_interval` (default 60) and `compact_threshold` (default 100) parameters. Added `_maybe_compact()` method called after substep loop in `step_frame()`.\n- **`fallingsand3d/test_compact.py`** - 19 tests covering all acceptance criteria.\n\n### Acceptance criteria met:\n- Compaction runs every 60 frames (configurable) when dead_count > 100\n- Non-DEAD particles moved to front of all SoA arrays\n- `_high_water` updated to count of alive particles only\n- Physics kernels already process `[0, _high_water)` range (no change needed)\n- Tests: 10K kill+compact shows only alive particles, data preservation verified, simulation continues correctly after compaction\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- Uses sorted_* buffers as scratch space for the gather-copy-back pattern (avoids temporary allocations)\n- Dead particle detection via `(packed_info & 0xFF) != 0` handles both `packed_info=0` (from kill_in_sphere) and `packed_info=0x300` (from Reactions kernel)\n- Zeroes dead tail after compaction to prevent stale data\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":337,"cache_read_input_tokens":102605,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":337},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"p